&lt;p&gt;Enumerate is hiring a Payments Enablement Consultant to bring a deep expertise in digital payments and adoption to our implementation team. As a trusted advisor, this position empowers clients to fully utilize our platform, guiding them through a seamless transition to automated solutions that boost efficiency and growth. This position spearheads the onboarding process, closely collaborating with our Software Onboarding Managers, as well as other payment experts. Your mission will be to play a pivotal role in educating clients on effective software utilization, sharing best practices, and providing ongoing support throughout their implementation journey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide expert guidance and support to new and existing customers for adopting and growing digital payments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actively manage the digital payments implementation process and work with clients and third parties to ensure a smooth implementation and acceleration towards first transactions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Once live, continue to engage with the customers over next 90 days to accelerate and adopt electronic transactions. Monitor transaction penetration over 90 days via monthly reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for obtaining key metrics that have been identified for digital payments and providing an in-depth transition plan to Customer Success and Support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Educating clients on how to use the Enumerate Digital Payment offerings, including specific accounts receivable and accounts payable functions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with team members for regular transactional processes and reporting needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve payment success for existing clients by optimizing the payments process across the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the effective communication with clients and internal stakeholders while the customer is in Onboarding.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide digital payment training and end user support during and after the implementation process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meeting digital payment project deadlines as assigned by a Project Manager as well as schedule meetings directly with clients to move the projects forward.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Qualifications&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of experience understanding payments workflows and implementation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of accounts receivable and accounts payable workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Subject area knowledge in property management and accounting software a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel of 5% expected for quarterly team meetings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work in the US without sponsorship.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;The pay range is inclusive of base salary plus any applicable bonuses or commissions.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Total compensation pay range (annual salary):&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$55,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$65,000 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Enumerate is a leader in the property management space offering a robust ERP system called Central that delivers Community Accounting, Management, Communications, Engagement and Reporting all on one easy to use platform. It is the most comprehensive solution for property management, powerful enough to support large scale Property Managers, yet easy enough for Self-Management Associations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Enumerate, we put the Customer First in everything we do, delivering customer-centric solutions and finding ways to say YES! We aim to win and act on our goals and vision with the right amount of planning and execution. We have an incredible team atmosphere where egos don’t exist, and we credit others for contributions, accomplishments and success!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are actively looking for an experienced Product Manager who will contribute to defining our strategy and vision for our homeowner and resident engagement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define, prioritize and execute product roadmap that delivers robust Resident Engagement capabilities for Property Managers and Self-Management Associations and their customers, all in collaboration with designers, engineers, SMEs, and Product.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with the Engineering organization to set prioritization and backlog of work. Share ownership of Agile ceremonies, including Sprint Planning, Sprint Reviews, Backlog refinement and release planning. Drive the backlog details, user stories, and priority.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive strategy and execution across core resident engagement areas, including:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive AI-powered automation of core workflows including data ingestion, classification, and workflow orchestration--reducing the workload of our customers and end users&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and deliver GenAI-powered capabilities such as copilots, assistants, and agent-based workflows embedded directly into core product experiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enable predictive and prescriptive insights that help customers proactively manage communities, optimize workflows, and scale without increasing headcount&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement new avenues for driving adoption and utilization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, evaluate, and partner with third-party solutions that can accelerate product development and scale offerings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Migrate off of legacy platforms to a consolidated, forward-looking product experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver&amp;nbsp;successful mobile app products, with a strong understanding of mobile user experience and platform best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support go-to-market activities that enable Marketing, Sales, Customer Success and Operations to drive product adoption and grow revenue.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and publish easy to consume customer-facing materials, presentations, articles and webinars that drive awareness and adoption of Resident Engagement capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Directly partner with new and existing customers to understand Resident Engagement capabilities, processes and challenges customers face with a variety of workflows. Work with Product Leadership to incorporate Customer Feedback into solutions that remove friction and expand product value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain clear documentation of use cases, product goals, user impact, risk, scope, KPIs, and customer outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate actively in Agile ceremonies and practices to ensure delivery with quality and impact. This includes authoring epics, features, user stories, acceptance criteria, and supporting backlog refinement, sprint planning, standups, testing, retrospectives, and release planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Engineering, Data, Architecture, and Design teams to deliver scalable, secure, explainable, and production-ready solutions.&lt;/l

&lt;p&gt;Enumerate is hiring a Relationship Manager to serve as a trusted advisor and partner for our clients. This role is responsible for managing client requests and providing timely and results-based customer service. The Relationship Manager acts as a liaison between our clients and our internal teams, including Accounts Payable, Accounts Receivable, Operations, and Support. This role is responsible for the project management of client requests to ensure transparent communication and a timely resolution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates for this role must be located in the United States and able to work EST or CST time zones. This role can be hybrid or remote. If remote, this role requires travel every other month to Fort Lauderdale, Florida.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the voice of the customer and navigate internal processes with stakeholders from various teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide support to associations, granting users access to Enumerate Central and triaging issues as they arise&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a liaison between clients and internal teams, working with the client to gather the information and documentation needed by internal teams to set up bank accounts and complete reconciliations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with challenging customer requests or issue escalations as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Answer customer questions in a timely and accurate manner via phone or Zendesk ticketing system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assess customer needs and communicate feedback to peers and leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams to resolve customer requests in a timely and effective manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track key performance indicators related to client relationships, such as customer satisfaction, retention rates, and revenue growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a strong understanding of customer needs and a commitment to delivering exceptional customer service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of experience in Customer Success or Account Management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong customer service and project management skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to organize a daily workload by priorities and to meet deadlines in a fast-paced quickly changing environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience using Asana or other project management tools is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A background in accounting, bookkeeping or community association management is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;The pay range is inclusive of base salary plus any applicable bonuses or commissions.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Total compensation pay range (annual salary):&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$55,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$65,000 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a Senior Site Reliability Engineer who can own the architecture, governance, and cost efficiency of our cloud and platform infrastructure. In this role you’ll design and evolve our production environments, define standards and best practices, and partner with engineering and IT teams to build scalable, reliable systems that are easy to operate and cost-effective to run.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll be a hands-on technical leader: designing reference architectures, building CI/CD and automation pipelines, leading incident response practices, and setting guardrails around security, reliability, and cost management across our platforms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is a remote contractor role. We are seeking candidates located in LATAM.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Architecture &amp;amp; Infrastructure Ownership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, implement, and evolve cloud infrastructure architectures for high availability, reliability, security, and scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and maintain reference architectures and patterns for services, applications, and environments across the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop workflow processes and standards for building, deploying, and maintaining applications within a distributed architecture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead infrastructure modernization initiatives (e.g., containerization, Kubernetes adoption, infrastructure as code, platform consolidation).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Governance, Standards &amp;amp; Cost Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and enforce governance standards for infrastructure, CI/CD, observability, and operational practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and maintain policies for environment management, access control, configuration management, and change management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement cost management practices (e.g., tagging, budget alerts, rightsizing, reservations/committed use, auto-scaling policies) to optimize cloud spend.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with product and engineering leadership to balance performance, reliability, and cost-efficiency across environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use DORA metrics and industry benchmarks to drive continuous improvement in delivery and operational performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CI/CD, Automation &amp;amp; Operations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, implement, and maintain CI/CD pipelines for multiple applications and environments using tools such as Git, Azure DevOps, GitLab, or Jenkins.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and manage automation pipelines for deployment, configuration, and infrastructure management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain monitoring, alerting, and logging systems to ensure visibility, high availability, and performance of applications and services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage cloud infrastructure resources and services to ensure reliability, security, and scalability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Incident Management &amp;amp; Reliability&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead incident response efforts, including triage, root cause analysis, and post-incident reviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to and maintain incident response processes, runbooks, and on-call practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with engineering teams to design resilient systems and reduce mean time to recovery (MTTR).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Leadership, Mentorship &amp;amp; Cross-Functional Collaboration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with software engineering, QA, product, and IT teams to determine the best way to tackle complex infrastructure, security, and delivery challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor engineers in DevOps and platform practices, tools, and standards across the organization.&lt;/l

